The National Association of Nigerian Students (Zone D) has called for justice for a student of Obafemi Awolowo University, Ile-Ife, Heritage Ajibola who died after falling into a soakaway in BVER, one of the private hostels in the students’ village. The deceased, a student of the department of Linguistics and African Languages, was said to be with her friends spreading clothes on a line when she mistakenly fell into a hole leading into the soakaway and got stuck in it.  It was later discovered that termites had eaten the wood which was used to cover the soakaway. Reacting, Adegboye Emmanuel Olatunji, Coordinator of NANS (Zone D), in a statement, offered his condolences to the family of the deceased. Olatunji berated the school management for failing to check structural standard of hostels before allocating them to students. The statement read, “It is actually a sad reality to receive the loss of Heritage Ajibola who happens to be a 200L student of the Obafemi Awolowo University, from the Linguistics and African Languages department who accidentally fell into the soakaway during the mid-period of 9th February 2022 at Bver Hostel, Maintenance Ede Road, due to negligence and poor hostel management by the manager (Mr. Emmanuel) and the owner.



